===貿易===
鹽可能早已在新石器时代[[安那托利亞|安那托利亞]]的[[黑曜岩|黑曜岩]]交易中用作[[以物易物|以物易物]]<ref>{{cite journal |title=The role of salt in the formation of the Anatolian culture |url=http://www.academia.edu/2340259/Anadolu_Kultur_Olusumunda_Tuzun_Rolu-_The_Role_of_Salt_in_the_Formation_of_the_Anatolian_Culture |last2=Basobuyuk |first2=Zeynel |journal=Batman University: Journal of Life Sciences |issue=1 |year=2012 |volume=1 |pages=45–54 |last1=Golbas |first1=Alper |deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131211234508/http://www.academia.edu/2340259/Anadolu_Kultur_Olusumunda_Tuzun_Rolu-_The_Role_of_Salt_in_the_Formation_of_the_Anatolian_Culture |archivedate=2013-12-11 |access-date=2016-08-24 }}</ref>。随着文明的传播，鹽成为了世界主要贸易商品之一。大約在公元前2800年，埃及人開始以鹹魚交易[[腓尼基|腓尼基]]人的杉木、玻璃以及[[骨螺紫|骨螺紫]]的染料。腓尼基人同时也和夥伴們交易埃及的鹹魚、[[北非|北非]]的鹽等商品。他们的贸易王国遍布整个[[地中海|地中海]]<ref name="Kurlansky2002" />{{rp|44}}。在公元前1000年期間，凱爾特人的社區透过與[[古希腊|古希腊]]及[[古罗马|古罗马]]交易鹽和[[咸肉|咸肉]]致富，並與它們換取葡萄酒和其他奢侈品{{sfn|Barber|1999|p=136}}。[[希羅多德|希羅多德]]在公元前5世紀描写了穿越[[利比亚|利比亚]]的食鹽贸易路线。[[罗马帝国|罗马帝国]]早期修建了从[[奥斯提亚|奥斯提亚]]的[[盐盘|盐盘]]到首都的[[撒拉里道|撒拉里道]]，以运送食鹽<ref name="Time Magazine">{{cite news |url=http://content.time.com/time/magazine/article/0,9171,925341,00.html |title=A brief history of salt |date=1982-03-15 |newspaper=Time Magazine |accessdate=2013-10-11 |deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160509161416/http://content.time.com/time/magazine/article/0%2C9171%2C925341%2C00.html |archivedate=2016-05-09 }}</ref>。在古代，鹽巴對於[[希伯來人|希伯來]]、[[希臘人|希臘]]、[[羅馬人|羅馬]]、拜占庭、[[赫梯人|赫梯]]和[[埃及人|埃及]]等人來說皆是珍品。食鹽成為一項重要的貿易品，當時的人們會把食鹽經[[地中海|地中海]]船運，運經特地為食鹽而建的道路，再以{{link-en|駱駝隊|Camel train}}穿過[[撒哈拉|撒哈拉]]<ref>{{cite book|author=Pierre Laszlo|title=Salt: Grain of Life|url=https://books.google.com.hk/books?id=p6irAgAAQBAJ&pg=PA17&dq=Salt+Sahara++camel+caravans&hl=zh-TW&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwiYpsSYrZ7QAhVHWbwKHdVRACcQ6AEIJDAB#v=onepage&q=Salt%20Sahara%20%20camel%20caravans&f=false|publisher=Harper Perennial|isbn=9780060084684|page=22|date=2002-06-04|access-date=2016-11-10|archive-date=2021-05-17|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210517034016/https://books.google.com.hk/books?id=p6irAgAAQBAJ&pg=PA17&dq=Salt+Sahara++camel+caravans&hl=zh-TW&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwiYpsSYrZ7QAhVHWbwKHdVRACcQ6AEIJDAB#v=onepage&q=Salt%20Sahara%20%20camel%20caravans&f=false|dead-url=no}}</ref>。在[[撒哈拉以南非洲|撒哈拉以南非洲]]，鹽曾作為貨幣使用，例如在[[埃塞俄比亚|埃塞俄比亚]]岩鹽磚曾被用作硬幣<ref name="EB" />。在6世纪的[[摩尔人|摩尔]]商人手里，盐可以与等质量的黄金交换<ref name="Time Magazine" />。傳統上，[[圖瓦雷克人|圖瓦雷克人]]维護著一條橫越[[撒哈拉沙漠|撒哈拉沙漠]]的路線，特別是{{le|鹽馬幫|Azalai}}用以運輸鹽的路線。雖然現今在尼日爾南部的馬幫們往返[[比爾馬|比爾馬]]时依然会穿越沙漠，但是大部分的貿易都是以卡車運輸。每隻駱駝前往比爾馬時帶着兩捆[[饲料|饲料]]和兩份貿易品，返回时則馱著對方用來交換的鹽柱和海棗<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.bradshawfoundation.com/africa/tuareg_salt_caravans/ |title=Tuareg Salt Caravans of Niger, Africa |accessdate=2013-10-11 |last=Paolinelli |first=Franco |publisher=Bradshaw Foundation |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160803184735/http://www.bradshawfoundation.com/africa/tuareg_salt_caravans/ |archivedate=2016-08-03 }}</ref>。

===稅收與戰爭===
据说[[克里斯托弗·哥伦布|克里斯托弗·哥伦布]]的航海活动就是用[[西班牙|西班牙]]南部的盐税资助的<ref name=Cowen/>。而在貿易路線以陆路为主的城市会徵收[[關稅|關稅]]<ref name="Cowen" />，[[利物浦|利物浦]]等城鎮也会通过出口從柴郡的鹽礦中提取的鹽以帶動經濟的發展<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.igg.org.uk/gansg/12-linind/salt.htm |title=Salt |last=Smith |first=Mike |year=2003 |work=Goods & Not So Goods: Lineside Industries |accessdate=2013-10-15 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20111124114738/http://www.igg.org.uk/gansg/12-linind/salt.htm |archivedate=2011-11-24 |deadurl=yes }}</ref>。鹽也引发了不少冲突与战争。有些國家之間為了食鹽而動起干戈。[[威尼斯|威尼斯]]便曾与[[熱那亞|熱那亞]]为鹽而戰，并贏得胜利<ref name="Cowen" />。鹽在[[美國革命|美國革命]]中也起到了重要的作用：美國的抗爭積極分子中便有製盐者；英國的一部分戰略是否認來自美國的反叛者帶了鹽過去<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.seasalt.com/salt-101/history-of-salt/ |title=History Of Salt |publisher=SaltWorks |accessdate=2016-11-10 |deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161107165407/https://www.seasalt.com/salt-101/history-of-salt/ |archivedate=2016-11-07 }}</ref>。高昂的[[加貝爾|鹽稅]]也是[[法国大革命|法国大革命]]的起因之一。但在法国大革命鹽稅廢除不久後，[[拿破仑一世|拿破仑一世]]便成為了皇帝，並宣布重新課徵[[加貝爾|鹽稅]]以应对對外戰爭的開支。直到1945年法國鹽稅才被再度廢除<ref name="Cowen">{{cite web |url=http://mygeologypage.ucdavis.edu/cowen/~gel115/salt.html |title=The Importance of Salt |last=Cowen |first=Richard |date=1999-05-01 |accessdate=2013-10-15 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160507083302/http://mygeologypage.ucdavis.edu/cowen/~GEL115/salt.html |archivedate=2016-05-07 }}</ref>。1930年，为了抗议[[英属印度|英国殖民统治]]下的{{tsl|en|History of the British salt tax in India||食鹽專營制度}}，[[圣雄甘地|圣雄甘地]]率领了100,000名以上的支持者举行了名为“[[食盐进军|盐进军]]”的抗议活动。他们走至海邊，将海水煮沸以取得盐类。这种[[公民不服從|公民不服從]]的精神激励了成千上万的普通百姓，并让[[印度独立|印度独立]]从精英人士的主张变为了全国性的运动<ref>{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=Er59fRsspgoC|title=Gandhi: Selected Political Writings|last=Gandhi|first=Mahatma|last2=Dalton|first2=Dennis|date=1996-01-01|publisher=Hackett Publishing|year=|isbn=0872203301|location=|pages=p. 72.|language=en|access-date=2016-09-06|archive-date=2016-08-10|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160810152615/https://books.google.com/books?id=Er59fRsspgoC|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

==成分與作用==
鹽的主要成分是[[氯化鈉|氯化鈉]]，而其他成分則來源於生產過程中的殘留物質，或是有意添加的，如防止結塊的[[抗結劑|抗結劑]]。

===氯化鈉===
{{main|氯化钠}}

钠離子是一种在人体中有重要作用的电解质，為神经和肌肉正常活动之所需，还能维持体内的[[渗透压|渗透压]]<ref>{{cite news|title=Dietary sodium|publisher=MedLinePlus|url=https://medlineplus.gov/sodium.html|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160728044421/https://medlineplus.gov/sodium.html|archivedate=2016-07-28|deadurl=yes|accessdate=2016-09-03}}</ref>。人类[[膳食|膳食]]中大多数的钠来自食鹽<ref name=CDC>{{cite web |url=http://www.cdc.gov/salt/ |title=Most Americans should consume less sodium |work=Salt |publisher=[[美国疾病控制与预防中心|美国疾病控制与预防中心]] |accessdate=2013-10-17 |deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160820212008/http://www.cdc.gov/salt/ |archivedate=2016-08-20 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bjchfp.gov.cn/bmfw/jkzs/jksh/201401/t20140106_162513.htm|title=减少膳食中的钠盐有助于控制血压|publisher=北京市卫生和计划生育委员会|date=2014-01-06|accessdate=2016-08-26|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161108133615/http://www.bjchfp.gov.cn/bmfw/jkzs/jksh/201401/t20140106_162513.htm|archive-date=2016-11-08|dead-url=yes}}</ref>。

食鹽中钠的质量分数略低于40%，所以6克（1勺）盐中含钠2,300毫克<ref name="USDA">{{cite web |url=http://ndb.nal.usda.gov/ndb/foods/show/277 |title=National Nutrient Database for Standard Reference, Basic Report: 02047, Salt, table |publisher=[[美国农业部|美国农业部]] |work=Agricultural Research Service, National Nutrient Database for Standard Reference, Release 27 |accessdate=2015-01-08 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160426013021/https://ndb.nal.usda.gov/ndb/foods/show/277 |archivedate=2016-04-26 |df= }}</ref>。西方国家每人每天摄入约10克食鹽，而东欧和亚洲国家摄入量较低<ref name=Strazzullo/>。很多加工食品含钠量较高，摄取后会显著增加钠的摄入量<ref name=":1" />。美国人摄入的钠中有75%来自加工食品和饭店菜肴，11%来自家庭烹饪和调味，其余则是食物中天然存在的<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.cdc.gov/salt/food.htm |title=Sodium and food sources |work=Salt |publisher=美国疾病控制与预防中心 |accessdate=2013-10-17 |deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160728154740/http://www.cdc.gov/salt/food.htm |archivedate=2016-07-28 }}</ref>。

因为鈉摄入过多会增加罹患[[心血管疾病|心血管疾病]]、[[中風|中風]]和[[腎病變|腎病]]的风险<ref name=IOM2013/><ref name=CDC/><ref name=Strazzullo>{{cite journal |last1= Strazzullo |first1=Pasquale |last2=D’Elia |first2=Lanfranco |last3=Kandala |first3=Ngianga-Bakwin |last4=Cappuccio |first4=Francesco P. |year=2009 |title=Salt intake, stroke, and cardiovascular disease: meta-analysis of prospective studies |journal=British Medical Journal |volume=339 |issue=b4567 |pages=b4567 |doi=10.1136/bmj.b4567 |pmc=2782060 |pmid=19934192}}</ref>，卫生机构普遍建议人们降低膳食中食鹽的摄入量<ref name=CDC/><ref name=WHO2013/><ref name=He2013/><ref name="aha">{{cite web |url=http://www.heart.org/HEARTORG/HealthyLiving/HealthyEating/Nutrition/Sodium-and-Salt_UCM_303290_Article.jsp#.V1jHedQrJkg |title=Sodium and salt |publisher=American Heart Association |date=2016 |accessdate=2016-06-08 |deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160817025149/http://www.heart.org/HEARTORG/HealthyLiving/HealthyEating/Nutrition/Sodium-and-Salt_UCM_303290_Article.jsp#.V1jHedQrJkg |archivedate=2016-08-17 }}</ref>。有研究建议，限制食鹽摄入的长期目标应为每天3克<ref name=He2013/>。每天少摄入1,000毫克钠，心血管疾病发病率就降低30%<ref name=USDA2015>{{cite book |title=Scientific Report of the 2015 Dietary Guidelines Advisory Committee |date=2015 |publisher=[[美国农业部|美国农业部]] |page=7 |url=http://www.health.gov/dietaryguidelines/2015-scientific-report/PDFs/Scientific-Report-of-the-2015-Dietary-Guidelines-Advisory-Committee.pdf |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160418002033/http://health.gov/dietaryguidelines/2015-scientific-report/PDFs/Scientific-Report-of-the-2015-Dietary-Guidelines-Advisory-Committee.pdf |archivedate=2016-04-18 |access-date=2016-08-24 }}</ref><ref name=CDC/>。没有急性疾病的成人和儿童减少日常钠的摄入能降低血压<ref name=He2013>{{cite journal|last1=He|first1=FJ|last2=Li |first2=J |last3=Macgregor |first3=GA |title=Effect of longer term modest salt reduction on blood pressure: Cochrane systematic review and meta-analysis of randomised trials.|journal=BMJ (Clinical research ed.)|date=2013-04-03|volume=346|pages=f1325|pmid=23558162|doi=10.1136/bmj.f1325}}</ref><ref name=Abur2013>{{cite journal |last1=Aburto |first1=Nancy J. |last2=Ziolkovska |first2=Anna |last3=Hooper |first3=Lee |last4=Elliott |first4=Paul |last5=Cappuccio |first5=Francesco P. |last6=Meerpohl |first6=Joerg J. |display-authors=3 |year=2013 |title=Effect of lower sodium intake on health: systematic review and meta-analyses |journal=British Medical Journal |volume=346 |issue=f1326 |pages=f1326 |doi=10.1136/bmj.f1326 }}</ref>。低钠膳食还能改善[[高血壓|高血壓]]患者的病情<ref name=Gra2011>{{cite journal|last1=Graudal|first1=NA|last2=Hubeck-Graudal |first2=T |last3=Jurgens |first3=G |title=Effects of low sodium diet versus high sodium diet on blood pressure, renin, aldosterone, catecholamines, cholesterol, and triglyceride.|journal=The Cochrane database of systematic reviews|date=2011-11-09|issue=11|pages=CD004022|pmid=22071811|doi=10.1002/14651858.CD004022.pub3}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal|last1=Adler|first1=AJ|last2=Taylor|first2=F|last3=Martin|first3=N|last4=Gottlieb|first4=S|last5=Taylor|first5=RS|last6=Ebrahim|first6=S|title=Reduced dietary salt for the prevention of cardiovascular disease|journal=The Cochrane database of systematic reviews|date=2014-12-18|volume=12|issue=12|pages=CD009217|pmid=25519688|doi=10.1002/14651858.CD009217.pub3}}</ref>。然而，也有研究称没有足够证据表明每天钠摄入量低于2,300毫克和心血管疾病风险的关系<ref name=IOM2013/>。[[世界卫生组织|世界卫生组织]]建议成人每天钠的摄入量应少于2,000毫克（相当于5克食鹽）<ref name=WHO2013>{{cite web |url=http://www.who.int/mediacentre/news/notes/2013/salt_potassium_20130131/en/ |title=WHO issues new guidance on dietary salt and potassium |date=2013-01-31 |publisher=World Health Organization |accessdate=2013-10-17 |deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160720052736/http://www.who.int/mediacentre/news/notes/2013/salt_potassium_20130131/en/ |archivedate=2016-07-20 }}</ref>。美国建议一般人每天钠的摄入量应小于2,300毫克<ref name=CDC/>，而非裔美国人、高血压、糖尿病和慢性肾病患者以及51岁以上人士每天钠的摄入量应不超过1,500毫克<ref name=Health.gov2010>{{cite book |title=Dietary Guidelines for Americans, 2010 |date=2010 |publisher=U.S. Department of Agriculture and the U.S. Department of Health and Human Services |page=24 |url=http://www.health.gov/dietaryguidelines/dga2010/DietaryGuidelines2010.pdf |accessdate=2015-04-29 |quote=African Americans, individuals with hypertension, diabetes, or chronic kidney disease and individuals ages 51 and older, comprise about half of the U.S. population ages 2 and older. While nearly everyone benefits from reducing their sodium intake, the blood pressure of these individuals tends to be even more responsive to the blood pressure-raising effects of sodium than others; therefore, they should reduce their intake to 1,500 mg per day. |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160901170759/https://health.gov/dietaryguidelines/dga2010/dietaryguidelines2010.pdf |archivedate=2016-09-01 }}</ref>。

===碘===
[[碘|碘]]是人類需要的重要[[微量元素|微量元素]]之一，碘缺乏可能導致[[甲狀腺機能低下症|甲狀腺機能低下症]]（[[甲狀腺|甲狀腺]]分泌的[[甲狀腺素|甲狀腺素]]不足），或令成人出現[[甲狀腺腫|甲狀腺腫]]、兒童出現[[克汀病|克汀病]]<ref>{{Cite journal | last1 = Vaidya | first1 = B. | last2 = Chakera | last3 = Pearce | doi = 10.2147/DDDT.S12894 | title = Treatment for primary hypothyroidism: Current approaches and future possibilities | journal = Drug Design, Development and Therapy | pages = 1–11 | year = 2011 | pmid =  22291465| pmc = 3267517| ref = harv | volume=6}}</ref>。1924年起，為了解决前述這些病症，人們在一般食鹽中掺入[[碘化鉀|碘化鉀]]、[[碘化鈉|碘化鈉]]或[[碘酸鈉|碘酸鈉]]製得[[混合物|混合物]]，稱為「碘鹽」。有時亦會加入[[右旋糖|右旋糖]]來穩定碘質<ref>{{cite web |url=http://extension.psu.edu/food-safety/food-preservation/faq/canning-and-pickling-salt |title=Canning and Pickling salt |publisher=Penn State University |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130407164426/http://extension.psu.edu/food-safety/food-preservation/faq/canning-and-pickling-salt |archivedate=2013-04-07 |accessdate=2016-08-24 }}</ref><ref>{{Cite journal|title="When it rains it pours": endemic goiter, iodized salt, and David Murray Cowie, MD.|url=http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC1646845/|last=Markel|first=H|date=1987-02-01|journal=American Journal of Public Health|issue=2|volume=77|pages=219–229|issn=0090-0036|pmc=1646845|pmid=3541654|access-date=2016-09-06|archive-date=2021-05-17|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210517034102/https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC1646845/|dead-url=no}}</ref>。其中{{link-en|碘缺乏|Iodine deficiency}}是[[智能障礙|智能障礙]]最大的可避免原因<ref name="mcneil">{{cite news |url=http://www.nytimes.com/2006/12/16/health/16iodine.html |title=In Raising the World's I.Q., the Secret's in the Salt |last=McNeil |first=Donald G. Jr |date=2006-12-16 |work=The New York Times |accessdate=2008-12-04 |deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160717055238/http://www.nytimes.com/2006/12/16/health/16iodine.html |archivedate=2016-07-17 }}</ref>。在使用碘鹽的國家，碘鹽顯著降低了碘缺乏導致的病症<ref>{{cite web |title=Iodized salt |url=http://www.saltinstitute.org/Uses-benefits/Salt-in-Food/Essential-nutrient/Iodized-salt |publisher=Salt Institute |accessdate=2010-12-05 |year=2009 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130214101408/http://www.saltinstitute.org/Uses-benefits/Salt-in-Food/Essential-nutrient/Iodized-salt |archivedate=2013-02-14 }}</ref>。各国碘鹽中的碘含量和加入碘化合物的种类不尽相同，例如美国碘鹽含碘量为百萬分之46至77，而英国的建议标准为百萬分之10至22，[[中国卫生部|中国卫生部]]則规定各地可根据实际情况确定碘鹽含碘量，平均值在20-30毫克/千克，允许上下有30%的浮动<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.accessdata.fda.gov/scripts/cdrh/cfdocs/cfcfr/CFRSearch.cfm?fr=101.9 |title=CFR - Code of Federal Regulations Title 21 |date=2015-04-01 |accessdate=2016-08-25 |deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160513052251/http://www.accessdata.fda.gov/scripts/cdrh/cfdocs/cfcfr/cfrsearch.cfm?fr=101.9 |archivedate=2016-05-13 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Discussion Paper on the setting of maximum and minimum amounts for vitamins and minerals in foodstuffs |url=http://ec.europa.eu/food/food/labellingnutrition/supplements/documents/akj_en.pdf |publisher=Directorate-General Health & Consumers |accessdate=2010-12-05 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121103050102/http://ec.europa.eu/food/food/labellingnutrition/supplements/documents/akj_en.pdf |archivedate=2012-11-03 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://food.china.com.cn/2012-03/18/content_24923043.htm|title=食盐含碘量全国不再一刀切|publisher=中国网食品频道|date=2012-03-18|accessdate=2016-08-25|quote=去年9月，卫生部发布食用盐碘含量新的食品安全国家标准，此次调整对食用盐中碘含量的平均水平(以碘元素计)，由原来加工水平的35毫克/公斤下调至产品水平20毫克/公斤至30毫克/公斤。新标准缩小了食用盐碘含量的允许波动范围，由原来的35毫克/公斤±15毫克/公斤调整为食用盐碘含量平均水平的±30%。此外，新标准规定各地可结合本省人群碘营养水平供应一种、两种或三种碘含量的碘盐。|archive-date=2020-12-25|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201225060218/http://food.china.com.cn/2012-03/18/content_24923043.htm|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

===氟化物===
膳食中缺[[氟|氟]]可导致[[龋齿|龋齿]]发病率大幅增加<ref>{{Cite journal | last1 = Selwitz | first1 = R. H. | last2 = Ismail | first2 = A. I. | last3 = Pitts | first3 = N. B. | doi = 10.1016/S0140-6736(07)60031-2 | title = Dental caries | journal = The Lancet | volume = 369 | issue = 9555 | pages = 51–9 | year = 2007 | pmid =  17208642| pmc = | ref=harv}}</ref>。食鹽中添加[[氟化物|氟化物]]可减少蛀牙的发生，对尚未实行牙膏加氟和[[饮水加氟|饮水加氟]]的国家尤为有益，因此在这些国家也更为常见。例如[[法国|法国]]有35%的市售食鹽添加了[[氟化鈉|氟化鈉]]<ref name="UEOIC" ></ref>。

===抗結劑===
食鹽中通常會添加{{link-en|矽鋁酸鈉|Sodium aluminosilicate}}或[[碳酸鎂|碳酸鎂]]等抗結劑以防結塊。[[磷酸钙|磷酸钙]]、[[碳酸鈣|碳酸鈣]]、[[脂肪酸|脂肪酸]]、[[酸式盐|酸式盐]]、[[氧化镁|氧化镁]]、[[二氧化硅|二氧化硅]]、[[矽酸鈣|矽酸鈣]]及{{link-en|矽鋁酸鈣|Calcium aluminosilicate}}有時亦會被用作抗结剂。[[歐盟|歐盟]]與[[美國|美國]]的食品藥物管理機構均准許在上述兩種含[[铝|铝]]化合物中使用铝<ref>{{cite web |first1=Wilella Daniels |last1=Burgess |first2=April C. |last2=Mason |url=http://www.ces.purdue.edu/extmedia/HE/HE-625.html |title=What Are All Those Chemicals in My Food? |publisher=School of Consumer and Family Sciences, Purdue University |accessdate=2011-02-27 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20060211210829/http://www.ces.purdue.edu/extmedia/HE/HE-625.html |archivedate=2006-02-11 }}</ref>。[[亚铁氰化钠|亚铁氰化钠]]有時亦會被採用<ref name="hansard.millbanksystems.com"/><ref>{{Cite book |url=http://ec.europa.eu/food/fs/sc/scan/out70_en.pdf |title=Potassium- and sodium ferrocyanides |last= |first= |publisher=European Commission |year=2001 |isbn= |location= |pages=p. 3 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160603153544/http://ec.europa.eu/food/fs/sc/scan/out70_en.pdf |archivedate=2016-06-03 |access-date=2016-09-06 }}</ref>。

在食鹽加入抗结剂的做法最早始於1911年，當時使用的抗结剂是[[碳酸鎂|碳酸鎂]]，可以令鹽粒更自由地流動<ref>{{cite web |title=Morton Salt FAQ |url=http://www.mortonsalt.com/faq/#q3 |accessdate=2007-05-12 |publisher=Morton Salt |deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160820144056/http://www.mortonsalt.com/faq/#q3 |archivedate=2016-08-20 }}</ref>。1988年，[[英國|英國]]的食品化學成分、消費性產品與食品之{{link-en|毒性委員會|Committee on Toxicity}}認為亚铁氰化钠作為食品添加剂的安全性「暫時可接受」<ref name="hansard.millbanksystems.com">{{cite web |url=http://hansard.millbanksystems.com/written_answers/1993/may/05/table-salt |title=Discussions of the safety of sodium hexaferrocyanate in table salt |website=Hansard.millbanksystems.com |date=1993-05-05 |deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160304090336/http://hansard.millbanksystems.com/written_answers/1993/may/05/table-salt |archivedate=2016-03-04 |access-date=2016-08-24 }}</ref>。

===乾燥劑===
有些人會自行在鹽瓶中加上生[[稻米|稻米]]或蘇打餅等[[干燥剂|干燥剂]]<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.newton.dep.anl.gov/askasci/gen01/gen01420.htm |title=Rice in Salt Shakers |publisher=Ask a Scientist |accessdate=2008-07-29 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110314162037/http://www.newton.dep.anl.gov/askasci/gen01/gen01420.htm |archivedate=2011-03-14 }}</ref>，用來吸收水份及防止鹽粒结块<ref>{{cite web |url=http://ww3.komotv.com/story/1454284/food-freshness?redirected=true |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110820105950/http://ww3.komotv.com/story/1454284/food-freshness?redirected=true |archivedate=2011-08-20 |title=Food Freshness |publisher=KOMO News |accessdate=2011-07-08 |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

===其他===
在低鈉鹽中，將部分[[氯化鈉|氯化鈉]]以[[氯化鉀|氯化鉀]]取代，可在攝取量不變的情況下，減少鈉及增加鉀的攝取各約50%<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.cgh.org.tw/tw/content/magazine/nutrition/DL/nutr83.pdf |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150824110321/http://www.cgh.org.tw/tw/content/magazine/nutrition/DL/nutr83.pdf |title=認識食用鹽 |accessdate=2016-11-10 |archivedate=2015-08-24 |author= |work=國泰綜合醫院 |publisher= |language=zh-TW |deadurl=no }}</ref>。

在“双营养强化盐”中，同时添加了碘酸盐和铁盐，后者有助于缓解[[缺鐵性貧血|缺鐵性貧血]]<ref name="Westphal"/>。据估计，缺铁性贫血影响了40%出生于发展中国家的新生儿的心智发育。盐中常用的铁源为[[延胡索酸亚铁|延胡索酸亚铁]]<ref name="Westphal">{{Cite book | last1 = Westphal | first1 = G. | last2 = Kristen | first2 = G. | last3 = Wegener | first3 = W. | last4 = Ambatiello | first4 = P. | last5 = Geyer | first5 = H. | last6 = Epron | first6 = B. | last7 = Bonal | first7 = C. | last8 = Steinhauser | first8 = G. | last9 = Götzfried | first9 = F. | doi = 10.1002/14356007.a24_317.pub4 | chapter = Sodium Chloride | title = Ullmann's Encyclopedia of Industrial Chemistry | year = 2010 | isbn = 3527306730 | pmid =  | pmc = | ref=harv}}</ref>。另一种添加剂为[[叶酸|叶酸]]（即[[维生素|维生素]]B<sub>9</sub>），[[孕妇|孕妇]]在怀孕前期和怀孕中补充足够的叶酸能够降低{{tsl|en|neural tube defect|神经管畸形|}}和[[唇裂|唇裂]]胎儿的出生率<ref name="UEOIC" />。添加了叶酸的盐通常呈黄色<ref name="UEOIC" >{{Cite book | last1 = Westphal | first1 = G. | last2 = Kristen | first2 = G. | last3 = Wegener | first3 = W. | last4 = Ambatiello | first4 = P. | last5 = Geyer | first5 = H. | last6 = Epron | first6 = B. | last7 = Bonal | first7 = C. | last8 = Steinhauser | first8 = G. | last9 = Götzfried | first9 = F. | doi = 10.1002/14356007.a24_317.pub4 | chapter = Sodium Chloride | title = Ullmann's Encyclopedia of Industrial Chemistry | year = 2010 | isbn = 3527306730 | pmid =  | pmc = | ref=harv}}</ref>。

==用途==
食鹽的[[鹹味|鹹味]]是人类能感知的[[基本味道|基本味道]]之一<ref>{{cite web |url=http://users.rcn.com/jkimball.ma.ultranet/BiologyPages/T/Taste.html |title=The sense of taste |date=2013-03-16 |accessdate=2013-10-16 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160408080806/http://users.rcn.com/jkimball.ma.ultranet/BiologyPages/T/Taste.html |archivedate=2016-04-08 |df= }}</ref>。全球很多菜式皆有使用食鹽，也常常装在餐桌上的{{tsl|en|salt shaker|鹽瓶|鹽瓶}}中供食客调味，同時还是很多加工食品的添加物質之一。許多東亞國家的傳統調味品並非食鹽<ref>{{cite web |url=http://community.seattletimes.nwsource.com/archive/?date=20010729&slug=pfish29 |work=The Seattle Times |title=The Salt of Southeast Asia |accessdate=2011-07-07 |year=2001 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160303223708/http://community.seattletimes.nwsource.com/archive/?date=20010729&slug=pfish29 |archivedate=2016-03-03 |dead-url=no }}</ref>。在這些國家的傳統文化裡，食鹽的功能被[[酱油|酱油]]、[[魚露|魚露]]和[[蠔油|蠔油]]一类的調味品取代，且主要用於烹調，很少用作餐桌上的佐料<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.diet.com/g/asian-diet |title=Asian diet |publisher=Diet.com |accessdate=2013-07-07 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160611091524/http://www.diet.com/g/asian-diet |archivedate=2016-06-11 }}</ref>。

食鹽可以為食物提供[[防腐剂|防腐]]和[[香味|提香]]等功能，所以它存在於大多數的加工[[食物|食品]]中（如[[罐裝食品|罐裝食品]]、{{link-en|鹽藏|Salting (food)|鹽藏食品}}、[[醃|醃製食品]]和即食食品等），然而在青菜、水果等天然的食物裡卻幾乎不存在。生产[[黄油|黄油]]和[[奶酪|奶酪]]制品的过程中要用到[[乳制品用盐|乳制品用盐]]<ref>{{cite book |last=Pieters |first=A.J. |last2=Flint |first2=D. |last3=Garriott |first3=E.B. |last4=Wickson |first4=E.J. |last5=Lamson-Scribner |first5=F. |last6=Brackett |first6=G.B. |last7=Atwater |first7=H.W. |last8=Alvord |first8=H.E. |last9=Withcombe |first9=J. |last10=Howard |first10=L.O. |title=Experiment Station Work |publisher=[[美国农业部|USDA]] |series=Bread and the Principles of Bread Making |year=1899 |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=l85CAQAAMAAJ&pg=RA5-PA28 |accessdate=2015-11-17 |pages=28–30 |archive-date=2021-05-17 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210517034101/https://books.google.com/books?id=l85CAQAAMAAJ&pg=RA5-PA28 |dead-url=no }}</ref>。在电[[制冷|制冷]]技术出现前，[[食品保存|食品保存]]的主要方法就是用鹽腌制。如新鲜[[鯡魚|鯡魚]]每100克中含有67毫克的钠，而[[腌魚_(英國)|腌制以后]]则含990毫克的钠；[[豬肉|豬肉]]每100克含63毫克钠，而[[煙肉|煙肉]]含1,400毫克钠；[[马铃薯|马铃薯]]每100克含7毫克钠，但[[馬鈴薯片|馬鈴薯片]]每100克含800毫克钠<ref name=HMSO />。飲食中食鹽的主要來源除了氯化钠之外，還有麵包和穀物製品、肉類製品和奶製品<ref name=HMSO>{{cite book |title=Manual of Nutrition |last=Buss |first=David |last2=Robertson |first2=Jean |year=1973 |publisher=Her Majesty's Stationery Office |isbn=0112411126 |pages=37–38}}</ref>。雖然人們從20世紀起已逐漸能使用罐裝和人工製冷的方式來保存肉類，但肉類仍是各類型食品中添加盐较多的<ref>{{Cite book |last=Barber |first=Elizabeth Wayland |year=1999 |title=The Mummies of Ürümchi |url=https://archive.org/details/mummiesofurumchi00barb |publication-place=New York |publisher=W.W. Norton & Co |isbn =0-393-32019-7 |oclc=48426519 |ref=harv}}</ref>。

